TITLE: Creating a Circle Component with Tamagui
DESCRIPTION: Defines a Circle component using Tamagui's styled function, including size variants and prop types.
SOURCE: https://github.com/tamagui/tamagui/blob/main/code/tamagui.dev/data/docs/guides/design-systems.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { GetProps, YStack, styled } from 'tamagui' // or '@tamagui/core' if extending just that

export const Circle = styled(YStack, {
  alignItems: 'center',
  justifyContent: 'center',
  borderRadius: 100_000_000,
  overflow: 'hidden',

  variants: {
    size: {
      '...size': (size, { tokens }) => {
        return {
          width: tokens.size[size] ?? size,
          height: tokens.size[size] ?? size,
        }
      },
    },
  },
})

export type CircleProps = GetProps<typeof Circle>
```

